sample.title: US announces start of phase two of Gaza peace plan | BBC News
sample.description:
US envoy Steve Witkoff has announced the start of phase two of President Donald Trump's plan to end the war in Gaza, with a technocratic Palestinian government established in the territory.
 
Under phase one, Hamas and Israel agreed a ceasefire in October, as well as a hostage-prisoner exchange, a partial Israeli withdrawal, and an aid surge.
 
Witkoff said the second phase would also see the reconstruction and full demilitarisation of Gaza, including the disarmament of Hamas and other Palestinian groups.
 
"The US expects Hamas to comply fully with its obligations," he warned, noting these include the return of the body of the last dead Israeli hostage.

sample.description:

sample.description:
Global temperatures in 2025 did not quite reach the heights of 2024, thanks to the cooling influence of the natural La Ni√±a weather pattern in the Pacific, new data from the European Copernicus climate service and the Met Office shows.
 
But the last three years were the world's warmest ever recorded, bringing the planet closer to breaching international climate targets.
 
Despite natural cooling from La Ni√±a, 2025 was still much warmer than temperatures even a decade ago, as humanity's carbon emissions continue to heat the planet, scientists have warned.
 
That will inevitably lead to further temperature records ‚Äì and worsening weather extremes ‚Äì unless emissions are sharply reduced, scientists warn have warned.
